notes: Scorers: JW Hamilton (Australia) and KV O'Neill (South Africa)
12th Men: A Symonds (Australia) and HH Dippenaar (South Africa)
Bevan/SR Waugh 4th wicket partnership 50 in 37 mins
Bevan/SR Waugh 4th wicket partnership 100 in 74 mins
Bevan/SR Waugh 4th wicket partnership 150 in 122 mins
Bevan/SR Waugh 4th wicket partnership 200 in 149 mins
SR Waugh's century was the 500th in One-Day Internationals, one ball after MG Bevan scored the 499th century.
South Africa innings: 1x5 ball over (38th over - Warne's 8th over, called by umpire Taufel)

milestones.description: Steve Waugh and Michael Bevan's 222-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 189 between Steve Waugh and Michael Bevan
Kallis has conceded the most runs in an innings (74) in ODIs for SA, going past Allan Donald's record of 72
